Diary
of my dear lovely mother 
written by her,

In Louisville Kentucky,
February 1-1861 to June 22-1861
In Chicago Illinois, 

June 23-1861 to November 25-1863
Elvira Cecilia Sheridan Badger. 
born in Charleston South Carolina April 4-1832
died in Chicago Illinois November 22-1911  underline ..underline
In some way, my oldest sister, Belle Sheridan Badger Harvey obtained possession of the Diaries of my Mother at the time of her death, when she was on a visit to her sister Julia Belle Sheridan Shreve (Mrs Thomas Taliaferra Shreve) temporarily staying on Delaware Place Chicago.
My parents having lived in the home of myself and wife from the year 1889 when they closed their home at 2106 Calumet avenue Chicago, until the death of my Father Aepheus Camillus Badger, which occurred on January 29-1908 in the home of myself and wife, Sarah Frances Cowles Badger, in Kenilworth Illinois, a suburb of Chicago my mother having also lived with my wife and self in our home with my Father until his death until said visit.
Although repeatedly requested and promising to send the Diaries of my mother to me, my said sister Mrs Turlington W. Harvey delayed and neglected to do so, until this Diary was received by me by mail this 9th day of September 1931 in Belvedere Marin County California-twenty years after the death of my Mother her Diaries for the years 1859 and 1860 reaching me through the same source August 24-1931 the ones she kept to the time of her death being still at this date forthcoming.
Alpheus Shreve Badger

Friday 1st Feb 1861.  Continuation of my Daily Journal kept 2 years- This has been a very ? day-raining & slippery- it is my boy Sheridan's Second Birthday (2 years old)- he was born at 12 oclock in the day- he is very smart talks very plain & almost everything-can run very fast- has twelve teeth- says some French words- very fair-blue eyes & light Hair- Virginia & ? came here today to tell me David Faulds Stone( my Brother inlaw) was burned last night- goods very much injured Thanks not very badly burnt- all of us at home tonight-it still rains
Saturday 2nd Feb 1861.
This has been a cloudy day-rained all night - not very cold-children learn at home  Belle & Eva have never been to school.  I teach them to read & write- also teach them their Sunday School lessons- my French girl Pauline teaches them French- they learn very fast- I also practise them in Dance every day- I do not approve of children being sent to school early- nine years is early enough- people ask me why it is that my children are so fat & rosy- I think it is because they exercise a great in the yard, and study little- they have learned from Pauline to Crochet well & embroider some-but they are not kept at it long- we went at 3 oclock to Masonic Temple to Dancing school- Mrs Wastell had a Fine lunch? aft- the children are wearing Union Badges a great deal- Our country in a very critical condition- people very much depressed- business very bad-

          Sunday 3rd Feb 1861.

This is a gloomy looking day- children gone to Sunday School - Pa took breakfast with me, I went to Calvary Church to hear the new minister Mr Everheart.  all of us in good health-

          Monday 4th of Feb-

A lovely day it is- children all took a bath and went out to play-after lessons- Pa came to see me- so did Virginia & children- Her baby Thomas is not well- he suffered much with cold- we are all in fine health-God has been very kind to us- I trust we will be thankful

          Tuesday 5th Feb-

Today has been a little damp- my little ones all went out playing-  Siss & sister Klingman? came to see me- Siss gave me some Presents-Mrs Feilder & Mrs J.G. Hitton called, sister Hilton invited me to a Calico Party at her Home- Mrs John Fergerson Mrs Henry Henghis- I went shopping, then to see Ma & Mother Balgem, children invited to a Fancy Dress Party at Lady Bulls 11th of Feb-

          Wednesday 6 Feb 1861-

Today was sunny but very windy- Sent all the children out playing- Siss came and took me and children out shopping- at 3 we went to see the Holman Troupe (consisting of 2 little girls & 2 boys- they Danced, played on the Piano & sang & acted in Opera- Belle & Eva took supper with Ma-Also Mrs Badger & myself took Tea with Mother Badger- after Tea went to Ma, for children, all well-

           Thursday 7 Feb 1861-

A bright day we having but very windy.  all well, out playing but Baby- he has a sore mouth.  Virginia came to see me- I sent the children & regret to Fayetta Bull & Party (Fancy Dress/ Mrs B & Belle learned? today to Chooch Bi??

            Friday 8 Feb 1861.

This has been a lovely day- my boys mouth better.  Belle & Eva & myself went out with Siss shopping- at 7 oclock went with Mrs Badger Belle & Eva to Sister Lacimier Hilton, to a Party Danced until11 then returned home all well-

X Saturday 9 Feb. 1861. Ada Danced first lesson
This has been a very beautiful day, last night after Mr. Badger had gone to Bed he had Pain
in his bowels, which caused him to have a strong Chill - he is pretty well this morning. 
After Breakfast I went to Dancing school, took Belle, Eva & Ada to Masonic Temple, 
crossed out letter Ada Commenced taking her first lesson from a Teacher in Dancing -- she's just 4?
years old -- Ms. Mastell was astonished how much she knew -- her sister taught her -- 
returned home to Dinner at [[8?

Sunday 17 Feb, 1861, X
There is snow on the ground today. I went to Mr. [] church this [] to see Ma. [] all well. Mrs. Badger gone. As his [], I went after tea to Mr. [] Church. 
Monday 18 Feb 1861.
This is a fair day. Virginia came to see me. She says [Siss?] is sick. My children all well - out walking. I went to see [Siss?] she in bed. [] [] cold. Wrote to Rhoda. 
Tuesday 19 Feb 1861.
Today is dreary & raining. [We?] all well.  Virginia came to see me. Making Ada a pink & white merino. [] is very gay at present. Many small parties. Calico parties masked parties & co. Brother Octane goes to many. I am making him now a [] [] for a Spanish costume. Ella Badger spent evening with []. It now blows up quite a storm. Mr. S.S. Moody died tonight of pneumonia [] [] sick. He leaves a wife & 4 children he was an excellent man.
Wednesday 20 Feb 1861.
This has been a bright day but windy. My children all well. I went at 3. oclock to Mrs. McGrearry's funeral at Christ Church. [] Sam Churchill daughter. Mr. E. Gunter gave [Belle?] her first lesson in music today. He was pleased with her progress X received a letter from Uncle Isaac Stanwood. Making a chapeau for [] F. Badger my Brother in Law today for a [masquerade?] at Louisville Hotel. Mr. Badger went to Church tonight I went to see Ma. Children took dinner with Ma.
Thursday 21 Feb 1861
This has been a very beautiful day. At 11 Oclock I wen to Sister Belle's house with all my children to spend the day. Sister Virginia took us there in her carriage. I went round to the house to see the Mr. Moody. He looked very natural. He was buried from the Presbyterian Church at 3 this afternoon. [Heard?] last night that Minnie [Midder?] was very ill with Scarlet Fever. Sent round today  X to inquire and she was dead. She is their only child. a beautiful lovely child my children loved her very much. and she loved them. Her parents [idolized?] her. She was a very pretty [dancer?]. a very lovely child. She was recovering from Fever. When their black girl caught [Fire?] and Mrs. [Midder?] in throwing water on the girl got some on Minnie which caused her to relapse. Mrs. Midder fell in trying to put out the Fire and broke her collar bone. It's very sad indeed. After I came home I [sent?] Belle & Eva to Grandma Badger to see Octane & Cousin Albert go to the Masquerade. While there we all set to work and made a [] [] for my [Husband?].
Friday 22nd Feb 1861.
This is a glorious day. [Warm?] & [dreamy?]. [Virginia?] came to see me early. I went at 11 Oclock with Ella Badger & all the children & Mr. Badger to Lawyer Johnsons Office opposite the Court house to see the raising of a new Union [stars?] & stripes Play. The Ground was []. The Military looked fine. A large band of Singers sung the Star Spangled Banner when the flag was unfurled. I suppose the number of people present must have been about [blank]. A glorious Demonstration. After the soldiers paraded. Everything went off very fine. 
Saturday 23rd
It has poured rain today. I am going in the Country to buy some Flowers to send to put on Minnie [Middlers?] Coffin. The lovely child is to be buried at 3 Oclock. The same hour that she used on every Saturday to [Wastells?] Dancing school [looking?] so beautiful and Dance so well. She was [] [young?] [and?] [lone?] [month?].

Sunday, 24 Feb 1861
This is a beautiful bright day -My Father (Mr Sheridan) too breakfast with us -Mr Badger and 
children gone to Unitarian Sunday School - I think I will go to the Christ Church Episcopal 
I took Ada to Church -Virginia brought us home in her Carriage- we went to Mr. Heywood's
Church -he discoursed on the lif of Washington -there was a beautiful piece on the
death of Minnie? Wilder -I stopped in to see Ma -we all very well-
Monday 25 Feb 1861
This was a beautiful day - Siss sent her Carriage for me at 11 to come there - my children
went riding with Virginia -children called on Mary Ten Broeck Anderson -and 
stayed to her Party - Mrs Dr Scott called on me, all of us well_ Maria Craik and Mrs. Cassiday
called.
Tuesday 26 -1861-
This has been a lovely day_ Children all in health _out buying new Hoops _they spent evening
at Grandma Badgers house_ Sister Belle came to see us- commenced making to
day blue worsted sacks for Bell & Eva -children took bath to day-
Wednesday 27 Feb 1861
This has been a very pretty day -quite warm- Siss called to tell me she would send her Carriage
to take us to Dr- Breckinridge's- I went and saw Kate & all her children - took Bell & Eva
with me - Mr Gunter gave Belle her second lesson -at half past nine in the Morning -at 4
Oclock took all children to see Little Holman children there was such a crowd we
could not get in Duffields & Floyds children here playing with mine_ Virginia
came to see me_   
Thursday 28 Feb - 1861
This is the last day of February - A very lovely day -my children all well - my boy went to spend
the day with Grandma Sheridan find time without Nurse in his life_ busy housecleaning
at 3 O clock went to see the Holman children _ they had a good house _ performed well
took all 4 of my children _ Horace & Eddie _ after Tea went with my husband to Musical Funclear
Concert -it very fine -
Friday March 1st 1861
This is an exceedingly warm day - still cleaning house - all well - went with Sister
Virginia & Belle to make calls - called on Mrs. Ten Broeck & Tom Andersons -then on Mrs
Dr Marshall - Misses Merriweather _ Mrs Watson Mrs Duvall. Dr Powells Hopkins - Grigleys- Mrs
George Merriweather. Garvine, Ella Cochran - children spent day with my Mother - Mrs Guult
& Benedict called to see me - Mrs Syrus Bent called - Sallie Garsien called on children -
Saturday March 2nd 1861
This has been a beautiful day -exceedingly warm- at 11 O clock I went with Belle and Eva to Dr
Masons the Dentists, we waited there until one before he came in - he has been ill
a long time - he is now suffering with Spine trouble and is going away to Water
Cure - he only looked at my teeth Virginia, & Sister Belles -but could not do the work
he x pulled Eva,s x two stomach teeth to let the first teeth come in, Eva cried very
much - they were very strong teeth - at 3 Oclock I went to Dancing School with Ada
She looked very lovely in her Scarlet Merino trimmed with black velvet -she 
danced all the quadrilles, Scotchish & Polka  Mary woke as well as any one
she has only taken 1 Lesson from a Teacher - her Sister taught her -she only 
4 years older - has very long curls - is considered very handsome- house cleaning
to day-
Sunday 3rd March 1861
The dark appearance of clouds threatens rain children & their Father gone to Sunday School
My Father took Breakfast with us - I went to Mr Heywoods Church with Ada - when we
returned home the wind blue very much and it rained - we all very well - Mr Badger
has gone to see his Sister Mrs Hittons - Ada came in contact with Whooping Cough last week.
